# LedgerCore

> Learn backend engineering by building a production-grade payments platform.

LedgerCore is a hands-on backend engineering curriculum where every concept is learned by designing, implementing, testing, deploying, and operating a real software system.

Rather than completing isolated exercises, learners incrementally build a production-grade double-entry ledger capable of processing financial transactions while applying modern software engineering practices used in industry.

---

# Goals

By the end of this curriculum you will be able to:

- Design scalable backend systems
- Build REST APIs and network services
- Model relational and event-driven data
- Write production-quality TypeScript and Java
- Apply software architecture patterns
- Build distributed systems
- Deploy applications using Docker and Kubernetes
- Create CI/CD pipelines
- Operate cloud-native applications
- Secure backend systems
- Monitor, profile, and optimize production services
- Design systems capable of handling large-scale workloads

---

# Learning Philosophy

The curriculum follows several core principles.

## Learn by Building

Every topic contributes to the same project.

There are no throwaway assignments.

Every week extends LedgerCore into a more capable production system.

---

## Engineering over Frameworks

Frameworks change.

Engineering principles remain.

The curriculum prioritizes:

- Computer Science
- Software Engineering
- System Design
- Distributed Systems
- Architecture
- DevOps

Frameworks are used only as tools.

---

## Production First

Every feature should be production ready.

Expect to write:

- tests
- documentation
- architecture decision records
- benchmarks
- monitoring
- deployment pipelines

---

## AI is a Reviewer, not a Replacement

AI is used to:

- review code
- compare implementations
- identify improvements
- explain trade-offs

The learner remains responsible for engineering decisions.

---

# Curriculum

The course progresses through seven phases.

| Phase | Focus |
|--------|-------|
| 1 | Foundations |
| 2 | Data & Persistence |
| 3 | Backend Engineering |
| 4 | Distributed Systems |
| 5 | Security & Reliability |
| 6 | Cloud & DevOps |
| 7 | Performance & System Design |

---

# The Project

Throughout the course you build a single system.

## LedgerCore

A production-grade ledger and payments platform supporting:

- Accounts
- Transfers
- Double-entry bookkeeping
- Balance calculations
- Transaction history
- Event publishing
- Authentication
- Observability
- Distributed deployment
- Cloud infrastructure

